00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:07.500
Hazelnut Cookies Recipe

00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:08.700
Makes 60 pieces

00:00:08.700 --> 00:00:09.500
Ingredients

00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:12.300
100 g (½ cup) butter

00:00:12.300 --> 00:00:14.500
100 g (½ cup) sugar

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:18.800
½ vanilla pod, seeds scraped out or 1 tsp vanilla extract

00:00:18.800 --> 00:00:20.500
Pinch salt

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:22.000
2 egg yolks

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.500
75 g (¾ cup) ground hazelnuts

00:00:25.500 --> 00:00:28.000
140 g (1 cup) flour

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:28.900
Ingredients for the topping

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:31.700
180 ml (¾ cup) cream

00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:34.000
75 g (1/3 cup) sugar

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
100 g (1/3 cup) honey

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
250 g (1 ¼ cup) hazelnuts, roughly chopped

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:41.200
Directions

00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:53.400
Beat the butter  until smooth then add the sugar, vanilla, salt and egg yolks and beat until well combined.

00:00:53.400 --> 00:01:05.600
Add the hazelnuts and the flour and mix until combined then bring the dough together

00:01:05.600 --> 00:01:10.300
and wrap it with plastic wrap and chill in the fridge for 1 hour at least.

00:01:10.300 --> 00:01:16.900
Place the dough on a piece of parchment paper and roll it out to 2-3 mm thick into a rectangle shape. 

00:01:16.900 --> 00:01:22.500
Place the parchment paper with the dough on a baking tray and chill again in the fridge for 1 hour. 

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:23.300
Directions for the topping

00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:30.300
Put the cream, sugar and honey in a pot and bring to a boil while stirring. 

00:01:30.300 --> 00:01:39.000
Leave boiling until golden and thick then add the hazelnuts and stir well.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Spread the topping over the dough and bake for 12-15 minutes in a preheated oven at 180°C.

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:58.500
Leave the petits-fours cool then let it chill for 20 minutes in the fridge then cut the petits-fours into small triangles.

